CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 18, 1955, pg. 1, reads: "$500 for NAACP - Dr. Charles Burks, right, of 549 Marshall Avenue, North Side, hands Mrs. Jimetta M. Andrews, left, a check for $500 for a life membership in National Association for the Advancement of Colored People, Tuesday, while Lou Davenport, the hard-working chairman of this year's local NAACP Membership Drive looks on approvingly. It is the third such contribution made during the campaign.  Mrs. Andrews is an executive board member and conscientious area leader in the drive. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Jimetta M. Andrews accepting check for NAACP from Dr. Charles Burks, with Lou Davenport standing between them, in office, another version
